<h1>Edit blog post</h1>

<%# rendering the partial again like in new.html.erb%>
<%= render partial: "form", locals: {blog_post: @blog_post} %>

<%# adding delete button in the edit page
    keeping the path ambigious again - rails figures it out 
    
    turbo javascript - automatically comes with rails 7 - it will ask for ok/cancel with string
    See /app/javascript/application.js - there is a line where hotwired/turbo is imported%>
<%= button_to "Delete", @blog_post, method: :delete, data: {turbo_confirm: "Are you sure?"}%>